 novel, The Silence. This exciting Companion is a genuine intervention in DeLillo scholarship by offering an interdisciplinary examination of his work across forms, media, method, and theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh1 aBarrett, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoxall, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConte, Joseph M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoughlan, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCowart, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunha Lewin, Katherine da, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonnelly, Kelsie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGander, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGander, Catherine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarland, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrigós, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGehlawat, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibbs, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroenland, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHering, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerren, Graley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoberek, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJelfs, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4h